 ('98', '114', 'en_us', 'New Entry', '<p>I\'ve been thinking for a while that estimating stories is a waste of time. I know, I know, I\'ve talked about <a href=\"{entry:110:url}\">estimating stories</a> in the past as if it were just a matter of course. And I stand by that post: If you\'re going to estimate stories, your points need to be consistent. However, I hypothesized that if you are breaking stories down to a small, consistent size, that measuring velocity by the number of stories should be roughly as accurate as using points. </p><p>Since this was simply a hypothesis, I started by gathering some data.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '1', '', 'http://', NULL, NULL, '', 'landscape', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, '2017-03-09 02:07:08', '2017-03-09 02:07:08', 'e680ba65-012d-4cab-bdbb-cbb8967a4a7f'),
