 ('239', '17', '5', '1', 'en_us', '8', '', '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Untitled\",\"slug\":\"untitled\",\"postDate\":1470706860,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"<p>This was a project in a painting class in college. The assignment was to create a painting by pouring paint on the canvas. This was the second iteration of this assignment. The first was criticized by the professor as being too layered. My professor didn\'t like that he cold tell the order that the paint was poured onto the canvas, though I&nbsp;disagreed. However, in the interest of getting a good grade, I&nbsp;pushed my painting as far from that criticism as I&nbsp;could. This was the result, which I&nbsp;have been incredibly pleased with.<\\/p>\",\"15\":\"\",\"14\":\"center top\",\"22\":\"portrait\",\"7\":[\"19\"],\"5\":\"<p>Acrylic on canvas.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Applied by mixing paint with water and pouring it onto the canvas. I&nbsp;then manipulated the canvas to force the paint to flow in different directions.<\\/p>\",\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-11-15 02:16:04', '2016-11-15 02:16:04', '273ace64-8a5a-48bb-b920-58f00d209689'),
